-- Malawi Tobacco Unchanged at $2.01 a Kilogram for Second Consecutive Week
-- Fred Ojambo
-- 2010-07-19T06:35:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/malawi-tobacco-unchanged-at-2-01-a-kilogram-for-second-consecutive-week.html

          
          
             The average price of tobacco in
Malawi, the world’s largest producer of burley tobacco, was
unchanged for a second week, Auction Holdings Limited said.  
 The leaf sold at an average $2.01 per kilogram (2.2 pounds)
in the week through July 16, the Lilongwe-based manager of
Malawi’s auction floors said in a statement published in the
Daily Times newspaper today. During the week, 9.4 million
kilograms of tobacco worth $18.8 million was sold, it said.  
 Since sales began on March 15, 145.3 million kilograms of
tobacco has been sold, generating revenue of $289.1 million. The
leaf has sold at an average of $1.99 per kilogram.  
